article.description: — Marlon Ruffin hit a pair of foul shots with 1.2 seconds left to lift Omaha to a 60-59 win over Middle Tennessee on Thursday.
article.headline: Ruffin leads Omaha over Middle Tennessee on late foul shots
article.linkText: Ruffin leads Omaha over Middle Tennessee on late foul shots
article.story: ESTERO, Fla. -- — Marlon Ruffin hit a pair of foul shots with 1.2 seconds left to lift Omaha to a 60-59 win over Middle Tennessee on Thursday. Ruffin finished with 18 points and Matt Pile had 16 for Omaha (1-1). Wanjang Tut added 10 points. Donovan Sims had 14 points for the Blue Raiders (0-1). Jordan Davis added 13 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
